<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 08 at 9:38PM CDT until July 08 at 10:00PM CDT by NWS Central Illinois</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1000 PM CDT
FOR SOUTHERN CLAY COUNTY...
At 938 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Xenia to 8 miles west of Cisne to near Helm,
moving southeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Clay City.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
